result.execSummary:
The defendant was charged with both OWI (2nd) and Operating w/ PAC >=0.15 (1st). The defendant was found guilty of OWI (2nd) and the other charge, Operating w/ PAC >=0.15 (1st) was dismissed by the court.

  • Traci L Murphy was found guilty of OWI (2nd), an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 346.63(1)(a).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: Per Statute 343.301(g) your operating privileges for operation of Class D vehicles will require that vehicles owned and/or driven by you be equipped with an ignition interlock device.  Must install a mandatory Ignition Interlock Device when defendant obtains an occupational license or regular license.  There is a $50 ignition interlock surcharge imposed.

records.addlTxt: DA Gerald Fox appears for the State.  Defendant appeared in person and with Attorney Betthauser.  Defendant plead no contest to amended count 2.  Court dismissed and read in count 1 for sentencing purposes.   Count 3 dismissed.   Court advised the defendant of the penalties of the charges she plead to.  She understood.   Elements reviewed by the court with the defendant.  Defendant understood.  Court reviewed the plea questionnaire, constitutional rights with the defendant.  Defendant understood.   Defense stipulated to a factual basis for the charges plead to.  Court found that the defendant freely, voluntarily and intelligently entered her plea and waived her constitutional rights.  Court found that a factual basis exists for the plea.  Court found the defendant guilty of amended count 2.  Joint recommendation for 18 mo. probation.  40 days jail.  All but 5 days stayed.  EMP allowed.  DL rev. 18 mo.  & IID.  $1,505.00 (includes DNA surcharge).  Attorney Betthauser requested minimum amount of probation.  Defendant did not elect to exercise her right to allocution.  Court ordered: sentence withheld, 18 months probation.   40 days jail.  All but 5 days stayed.  EMP allowed, according to jail rules.  Start on or before 60 days at 6 pm.  Driver's license revocation for 18 mo.  & 24 mo. IID.  $1,505.00 (includes DNA surcharge).  Alcohol assessment and driver's safety plan.
